    "windows-gfx1201": {
      "state": "validation-failed",
      "blocked": true,
      "blocked_reason": "MSM (Pippenger) requires cooperative kernel launch, which gfx1201 on TheRock ROCm 7.14 (Windows) does not support: hipDeviceProp_t.cooperativeLaunch=0 and hipLaunchCooperativeKernel returns hipErrorLaunchFailure (719) even for a 1x1 grid. NTT (7/7 fields) and the bn254 build-time gate PASS on gfx1201; only MSM is affected. This is a runtime/hardware capability gap (TheRock-7.14-Windows-gfx1201), not a port defect: gfx90a and gfx1100 report cooperativeLaunch=1 and pass MSM on Linux ROCm 7.2.1. The redundant Windows tier will be satisfied by validating on gfx1101 (RDNA3, supports cooperative launch). A non-cooperative MSM fallback is registered as deferred work sppark-msm-noncoop-fallback.",
